                        ['title' => 'Understand Purity Grades', 'text' => 'Research-grade peptides typically range from 95% to 99%+ purity. Higher purity means fewer impurities and more reliable results.', 'icon' => 'chart'],
                        ['title' => 'Learn to Read HPLC Reports', 'text' => 'HPLC (High-Performance Liquid Chromatography) separates and quantifies peptide components. The main peak represents the target peptide; smaller peaks indicate impurities.', 'icon' => 'document'],
                        ['title' => 'Verify Mass Spectrometry Data', 'text' => 'Mass spectrometry confirms the molecular weight of the peptide, verifying its identity. The measured mass should match the theoretical mass within an acceptable tolerance.', 'icon' => 'flask'],
