                'body' => "## Why Safety Matters\n\nPeptide research requires careful handling to ensure both researcher safety and experimental integrity. Contamination or improper handling can compromise results and pose health risks.\n\n## Essential Equipment\n\n- Nitrile gloves (powder-free)\n- Safety glasses\n- Lab coat or designated clothing\n- Alcohol swabs (70% isopropyl)\n- Sharps disposal container\n- Sterile syringes and needles\n\n## Sterile Technique\n\nMaintaining sterility is critical when handling peptides:\n\n- Clean all work surfaces before and after use\n- Wipe vial septa with alcohol and let dry\n- Use a fresh, sterile syringe for each session\n- Never reuse needles or syringes\n- Keep vials capped when not in use\n\n## Workspace Organization\n\nA well-organized workspace reduces the risk of errors and accidents:\n\n- Keep only the materials you need within reach\n- Separate clean and waste areas\n- Label everything clearly and immediately\n- Have a spill kit accessible\n- Work in a well-ventilated area\n\n## Emergency Procedures\n\n### Spills\n\n- Contain the spill immediately using absorbent materials\n- Clean with appropriate disinfectant\n- Dispose of contaminated materials as biohazard waste\n- Document the incident\n\n### Needle Sticks\n\n- Wash the area thoroughly with soap and water\n- Seek medical attention\n- Report the incident according to your protocol\n\n## Waste Disposal\n\n- Dispose of sharps in approved containers\n- Never recap used needles\n- Follow local regulations for chemical and biohazard waste\n- Do not pour reconstituted peptides down the drain",
