                'body' => "## GMP in Peptide Manufacturing\n\nGood Manufacturing Practice (GMP) ensures that peptide products are consistently produced and controlled according to quality standards. GMP covers all aspects of production from raw materials to finished product.\n\n## Key Quality Control Tests\n\n### Identity Testing\n\n- **Mass spectrometry** \u2014 Confirms molecular weight\n- **Amino acid analysis** \u2014 Verifies composition\n- **Sequencing** \u2014 Confirms primary structure\n\n### Purity Testing\n\n- **HPLC** \u2014 Quantitative purity assessment\n- **Capillary electrophoresis** \u2014 Complementary separation method\n- **LC-MS** \u2014 Coupled purity and identity confirmation\n\n### Impurity Testing\n\n- **Related substances** \u2014 Truncated sequences and byproducts\n- **Residual solvents** \u2014 From synthesis and purification\n- **Heavy metals** \u2014 From reagents and equipment\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\nGMP requires comprehensive documentation:\n\n- Batch production records\n- Standard operating procedures\n- Deviations and investigations\n- Stability data\n\n## Certificate of Analysis\n\nA GMP-compliant COA includes:\n\n- Batch number and manufacturing date\n- Test methods and specifications\n- Results for each quality attribute\n- Expiry date and storage conditions",
